frameDefinitions: A Sound emitted by a  Sound_source, which construed as a single point, moves along a Path.
A Theme moves on or against the surface of a Static_object.
A Phenomenon is portrayed with respect to the Degree of likelihood that it will  be perceived and known, given the (usually implicit)
An Agent causes a Patient to be more strong, often resulting in something that is more secure and safe.
An Obstruction blocks an Eclipsed entity partially or completely from view.
In this frame a Speaker ceases speaking, sometimes about a particular Topic.
frameExamples: Her shouts <t>echoed</t> around the cylinder formed by the walls.
It's abundantly <t>obvious</t> that we'll need to spend more time on public perception.
Local Serbs are <t>strengthening</t> their grip on a narrow corridor along the Sava River between two large Serbian areas.
A small green bulb <t>concealed</t> behind the panel flashed on momentarily .
Finally, Jan <t>shut</t> <t>up</t> about his car accident.
listRoleDefinitions: A percept produced  in hearing organs by  vibrations which travel through the air or another medium.
The location of the Sound_source from which the <fen>Sound</fen> travels
The Path of the Sound's movement is any description of its trajectory of motion which is neither a Location_of_sound_source or a Goal.
The point-like entity which produces the <fen>Sound</fen>.
A description of the location where the <fen>Sound</fen> ends up.
The time when  the <fen>Sound</fen> movement occurs.
A setting in which <fen>Sound</fen> movement happens.
The physical entity which moves over the suface of the <fen>Static_object</fen>
A non-moving physical object over a surface of which the <fen>Theme</fen> moves.
Two moving entities whose surfaces move against each other.
The setting in which the motion of the <fen>Theme</fen> happens
The entity or facts that are undeniable given the <fen>Evidence</fen>.
The gradable aspect of a <fen>Phenomenon</fen> which concerns how likely it is that the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> be known. This frame element is incorporated by the lexical units in this frame.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> from the norm or from the value for another <fen>Phenomenon</fen> in terms of how likely the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> would be known.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is obvious
The <fen>Agent</fen> fortifies the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity that is being made stronger.
An event which causes the <fen>Patient</fen> to become stronger.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> makes the <fen>Patient</fen> stronger.
The location at which the <fen>Agent</fen> fortifies the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The entity which blocks the <fen>Eclipsed</fen> entity from view.
The entity which is blocked from view.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> has previously been speaking but has now stopped.
The <fen>Expressor</fen> is the <fen>Speaker</fen>'s voice or other communicative noise emitted by the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the becoming silent occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the location where the becoming silent occurs.
listRoleExamples: The Prince 's laugh echoed <fex>from the corridor</fex>.

There was muzak echoing <fex>from cheap speakers</fex>.
<fex>In the mornings</fex> the harsh , squawking voices of the gulls echo between the channel walls
I heard their footsteps echo <fex>in the hollow cavern</fex>.
He felt <fex>his teeth</fex> scrape against the plaster
<fex>In the hallway</fex> a key grated in the lock
It is obvious for example <fex>that 9/10 is not the same as 1</fex>.
It is <fex>abundantly</fex> obvious you have not a clue how the Retro Program works.
It is obvious <fex>now</fex> that Senator O. T. Tawa has no plan.
The mists obscured <fex>the top of the tower</fex>.
